DOM REFERENCE:- https://www.w3schools.com/js/js_htmldom.asp
EVENT REFERENCE:- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/JavaScript/Building_blocks/Events

check more:-
-   Callback functions


To add, remove, toggle a class to the element using DOM use:-
- .classList.add()
- .classList.remove()
- .classList.toggle()
eg:- document.querySelector("h1").classList.toggle("huge")

To change the element text:-
- .textContent
- .innerHtml
eg:- document.getElementById("title").innerHtml = "Hello"

To manipulate the attributes:-
- .attributes()
- .setAttributes()
- .getAttributes()
eg:- document.querySelector("a").setAttribute("href","www.google.com")